Now I can see the file structure. I need to fix the unchecked return values from `asn_encode_to_new_buffer()` calls in three functions:

1. `s1ap_eNB_decode_initiating_message()` (lines 39-96)
2. `s1ap_eNB_decode_successful_outcome()` (lines 98-126)
3. `s1ap_eNB_decode_unsuccessful_outcome()` (lines 128-149)

The pattern I need to implement is:
1. Check if `res.result.encoded > 0` before calling `free(res.buffer)`
2. If encoding failed, log an error message with the procedure name and return `-1`
3. Only call `free(res.buffer)` if encoding succeeded

Let me start with the first function: `s1ap_eNB_decode_initiating_message()`:

For each case in the switch statement, I need to replace:
```c
res = asn_encode_to_new_buffer(NULL, ATS_CANONICAL_XER, &asn_DEF_S1AP_S1AP_PDU, pdu);
free(res.buffer);
```

With:
```c
res = asn_encode_to_new_buffer(NULL, ATS_CANONICAL_XER, &asn_DEF_S1AP_S1AP_PDU, pdu);
if (res.result.encoded > 0) {
    free(res.buffer);
} else {
    S1AP_ERROR("Failed to encode initiating message for procedure %s\n", "procedure_name");
    return -1;
}
```

Let me implement this for all three functions.

